licit, or to overide the document contexts you can use notation like this (+2y to David), or (+3x to David from Voz), or (+2y to David from Voz for facilitating the meeting on 22nd March). The code parsing the text should be intelligent enough to deal with this syntax. Effectively the currency-markdown is basically a form of legal-markdown that contains a currency DSL (domain specific language) withing bracketed text fragments that begein with a +or - followed by a number).\n\n"
